2.10	Gone_to_Earth_(Barclay_James_Harvest_album)	Gone to Earth (Barclay James Harvest album)	Gone To Earth is an album by the English rock group Barclay James Harvest released in 1977. It reached #30 in the UK charts, but in Germany it peaked at #10 and stayed for 197 weeks in the German album charts. It is ranked #6 on the list of longest running albums in the German album charts. Only the My Fair Lady soundtrack and albums by Simon &amp; Garfunkel (Greatest Hits), The Beatles (1962-1966), Pink Floyd (Wish You Were Here), and Andrea Berg (Best Of) spent more weeks in the charts. It was the band's largest selling album, eventually selling more than a million copies worldwide.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/34/Bjh_gonetoearth.jpg/220px-Bjh_gonetoearth.jpg
